The paper discusses planning problems with incomplete information and uncertainty, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning (cs.PL) research. The paper also proposes an offline analysis method for decision-making, which involves optimization and modeling, making it relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed method for real-time execution, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
